# DemandSpec Rules for Cursor

Use these rules when working on requirement documents, product specs, prototypes, acceptance criteria, AI scenarios, and development handoff tasks.

## Core Flow

Intake → Clarify → Diagnose → Model → Prototype → Specify → Validate → Handoff → Archive

## Required Practices

- Use `.demandspec/` for framework configuration and templates.
- Use `demands/<demand-id>/` for requirement assets.
- Mark missing information as `待确认`.
- Mark inferred information as `当前假设`.
- AI scenarios require `ai-fit-assessment.md`.
- Prototype work requires `figma-frame-spec.md`, `component-tree.md`, and `interaction-map.md`.
- PRD work requires acceptance criteria.
- Handoff work must split frontend, backend, algorithm, data, and test tasks.
